---
// Two-track timeline, matching docs/images/lag.png: LIVE MATCH races ahead,
// COMMENTARY trails a few seconds behind on the same track — by the time the
// viewer's (already-delayed) stream catches up to a moment, the matching line
// of commentary has had time to be written and rendered, so it lands in sync.
const liveEnd = 94;
const commentaryEnd = 68;
const BEAT_SEC = 60 / 135;
---

<section id="delay" class="relative px-6 py-16 sm:px-8">
	<div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
		<h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">
			Here's the clever part.
		</h2>
		<p class="mt-4 text-slate-400">It runs a few seconds behind the live action.</p>
	</div>

	<div class="relative mx-auto mt-10 max-w-3xl">
		<div class="flex flex-col gap-10">
			<div>
				<span class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-400">▸ live match</span>
				<div class="relative mt-3 h-2 rounded-full bg-slate-800">
					<div
						class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-500/40 to-amber-400"
						style={`width:${liveEnd}%;`}
					/>
					<span
						class="beat-dot absolute top-1/2 h-3.5 w-3.5 -translate-y-1/2 rounded-full bg-amber-400 shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(251,191,36,0.8)]"
						style={`left:calc(${liveEnd}% - 7px);`}
					/>
				</div>
			</div>

			<div>
				<span class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-widest text-cyan-400">▸ commentary</span>
				<div class="relative mt-3 h-2 rounded-full bg-slate-800">
					<div
						class="absolute inset-y-0 left-0 rounded-full bg-gradient-to-r from-cyan-500/40 to-cyan-400"
						style={`width:${commentaryEnd}%;`}
					/>
					<!-- pulses one beat behind the live dot — the same delay this whole
					     section is explaining, made visible in the animation itself. -->
					<span
						class="beat-dot absolute top-1/2 h-3.5 w-3.5 -translate-y-1/2 rounded-full bg-cyan-400 shadow-[0_0_16px_rgba(0,196,224,0.8)]"
						style={`left:calc(${commentaryEnd}% - 7px); animation-delay:${BEAT_SEC / 2}s;`}
					/>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>

		<!-- gap annotation: dotted connector dropping from the live dot down to the
		     commentary track, labeled with the realized delay. -->
		<div
			class="pointer-events-none absolute top-[6px] h-[88px] border-l border-dashed border-amber-400/50"
			style={`left:${liveEnd}%;`}
		>
			<span
				class="absolute top-1/2 left-3 -translate-y-1/2 whitespace-nowrap text-lg font-extrabold text-amber-400"
			>
				~3s
			</span>
		</div>
	</div>

	<p class="mx-auto mt-10 max-w-xl text-center text-sm text-slate-500">
		By the time the (already-delayed) stream reaches a moment, the line describing it has had
		time to be written and voiced — so it always lands in sync, never racing to catch up.
	</p>
	<p class="mx-auto mt-3 max-w-xl text-center text-sm text-slate-500">
		Streaming the game footage too? Hold it back by the same amount in OBS (stream delay or a
		render delay filter) so picture and call land together.
	</p>
</section>
